                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre and irregular. The handwriting tend to left-sloping;
                           it appears very irregular due to the variations in ruling (the size of the
                           columns and the space between lines often differs significantly: e.g.,
                           <locus target="#15ra">15ra</locus>, 23r, 28r, 35rb), changes of the pen
                           nib (slender or broad nib: e.g. <locus target="#1va">1va</locus>b), changes
                           in letters' height and varying spaces between the
                           letters.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid scarlet).</seg>
                        <date>Mid 18th - early 19th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Rubrication of the main text is executed in vivid
                           red. 
 Nomina sacra; original names of the donors (mostly erased);
                           incipit of Text I-1; a few lines on the incipit page of Text I-2, incipit
                           of its sections and subsections; incipit of Text I-3 and its sections
                           (fols. 16ra, 19rb, 22ra, 23rb, 29rb, 30va, 34vb, 37va, 39ra, 40rb, 41rb,
                           42va, 44ra, 49ra, 51ra) and of a subsection (fol. 26va); word ʾǝsaggǝd,
                           "I worship"; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Later hand of additions of new donor names</seg>
                        
                        <seg type="ink">red (strong amaranth, strong
                           vermillion).</seg>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Names of later donors, added (later) in a secondary hand,
                           are written in strong amaranth and strong vermillion.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#4v">4v</locus>: Black ornamental band;
                        interlaces.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#4v">f. 4v</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           
                           <note> The note is crudely written and hardly legible because the ink has
                              faded away. Hafta [sic] Gabrǝʾel with his father Walda Giworgis [sic]
                              and his mother Walatta Māryām are mentioned in the lower part of the
                              note. The upper part has been filled in by another secondary hand, in
                              strong amaranth ink, with the names of Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas Qǝddus and
                              his wife ʿĀmata Dǝngǝl. Furthermore a tabot (church) called Śǝllāse
                              ʾAyga is mentioned. It is possible that the same hand wrote Additio 2
                              in Ms. AMM-001 and Additio 3 in Ms. AMM-004. Both Mss. were donated by
                              Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas Qǝddus. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>- The name(s) of the original donor(s), mentioned
                           throughout the Ms., have been erased and partly replaced with other names
                           in a different hand.
</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>- Omissiones written interlineally or in the
                           margins: e.g., <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus>, 16ra, 20r, 50ra.</desc>
                        </item>
                           <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>-
                              Musical notation on <locus target="#45rb">45rb</locus> (?).</desc>
                        </item>
                              <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>-
                                 Corrections made in a secondary hand: e.g., <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus>, 15ra, 45r, 52vb.</desc>
                        </item>
                                 <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>- Most of the erasures marked with
                                    parallel lines: e.g., <locus target="#8ra">8ra</locus>, 23rb, 34vb, 37va.</desc>
                        </item>
                                    <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc> - Crude letters: <locus target="#4r">4r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Names of the days of the week indicating the
                              readings in Text I-1, in pen: fols. 2v, 3rv.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
