               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0064AMM">ʿĀddigrāt Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1830">Mid-18th - early 19th cent. (?)
                        
 Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas Qǝddus might be identified with <persName role="donor" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4996hagosSa">Ḫagos</persName> (d. 1831),
                        the second son of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8265Sabagadi">daǧǧāzmāč Sabāgādis</persName> (1770-1831) whose baptismal name was
                        Za-Manfas Qǝddus. The identification is based on Additiones 1 and 2 in Ms.
                        FBM-002.</origDate>
                     
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The name of the original female donor has
                     been erased throughout the Ms. Only the name of the donor's father, ʿAmda
                     Māryām, has been preserved (<locus target="#19rb">19rb</locus>, 30va).
                     Their names were partly replaced with those of Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas Qǝddus and
                     his wife ʿĀmata Dǝngǝl in strong amaranth ink (e.g., <locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus>, 19ra, 23ra, 29ra, 37va, 40rb; s. also Additio 1), occasionally
                     with that of Haftä (sic) Gabrǝʾel and Walatta Madḫǝn in strong vermillion and
                     black ink (e.g, <locus target="#19ra">19ra</locus>, 23rb, 30va, 41rb; s. also
                     Additio 1).</provenance>
               </history>
